---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy — Matej Lukášik"
  description="How this site handles contact form, booking, and analytics data."
  lang={lang}
  currentPath="/privacy"
>
  <section class="section-padding bg-surface">
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-heading mb-8">Privacy</h1>
      <div class="space-y-8 text-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Last updated: 19 July 2026. This notice explains how I handle personal data collected through this website, its contact form, booking flow, optional analytics, and technical hosting.
        </p>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Controller</h2>
          <p>
            The controller is Matej Lukášik, Business ID 50113801, Ulica Hlboká 5943/14, 917 01 Trnava, Slovakia, registered in the Slovak Trade Register no. 250-37148. You can contact me at <a href="mailto:matej@matejlukasik.com" class="text-primary font-medium hover:text-primary-hover">matej@matejlukasik.com</a> or <a href="tel:+421944302185" class="text-primary font-medium hover:text-primary-hover">+421 944 302 185</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">What I collect</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Contact form: name, email, selected service, message, language, and basic submission metadata needed to process the inquiry.</li>
            <li>Booking flow: when you open the Contact page, Cal.com receives the technical data needed to display and protect the booking calendar. If you make a booking, it also processes the details you enter, the selected meeting time, booking status, and related scheduling metadata.</li>
            <li>Analytics: only after consent, Google Analytics may receive aggregate page views, section views, clicks, scroll depth, conversion events, and campaign parameters. Form content and booking identifiers are not sent to analytics.</li>
            <li>Hosting and security: Cloudflare may process technical request data such as IP address, user agent, URLs, timestamps, and security events needed to deliver and protect the site.</li>
            <li>Fonts: when the site requests Google Fonts, Google may receive technical request data such as your IP address, browser information, and the referring page.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Legal basis</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Contact and booking data: Article 6(1)(b) GDPR when you ask me to take steps before a possible contract; otherwise Article 6(1)(f), my legitimate interest in responding to business inquiries and managing consultations.</li>
            <li>Analytics cookies are optional. Analytics cookies and Google Analytics use Article 6(1)(a), consent. You can withdraw or change this through Cookie settings in the footer.</li>
            <li>Hosting, security, spam prevention, operation of the booking calendar, service operation, and delivery of web fonts: Article 6(1)(f), legitimate interests in running a reliable, secure, and readable website.</li>
            <li>Legal or accounting records, where relevant: Article 6(1)(c) legal obligation or Article 6(1)(f) legitimate interests in handling claims and business records.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Whether you must provide data</h2>
          <p>
            You are not legally required to provide personal data. I need your email address and message to answer a contact inquiry, and Cal.com needs the fields marked as required to make a booking. Without those details, I cannot respond through the form or reserve a meeting. Analytics consent is entirely optional and refusing it does not limit the site.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Who receives data</h2>
          <p>
            I use service providers only where needed to run the site and respond to you: <a href="https://resend.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary font-medium hover:text-primary-hover">Resend</a> for contact form email delivery, <a href="https://cal.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary font-medium hover:text-primary-hover">Cal.com</a> for bookings, <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary font-medium hover:text-primary-hover">Cloudflare</a> for hosting and security, and <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary font-medium hover:text-primary-hover">Google</a> for web fonts and optional Google Analytics after consent. Email and calendar providers also receive data when needed to reply and schedule the call. Public authorities may receive data where the law requires it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">International transfers</h2>
          <p>
            Some providers may process data outside the European Economic Area, including in the United States. Where applicable, transfers rely on the European Commission's EU–US Data Privacy Framework adequacy decision for certified recipients. Otherwise, the providers' data processing terms and European Commission Standard Contractual Clauses are used, together with supplementary safeguards where required. You can request information about the safeguard relevant to your data by emailing me.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Retention</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Contact inquiries are kept while the inquiry or client relationship is active, and normally up to 24 months after the last meaningful interaction unless a longer period is needed for legal, accounting, or dispute reasons.</li>
            <li>Booking records are kept in Cal.com and calendar tools while needed for scheduling and follow-up, and normally up to 24 months after the meeting.</li>
            <li>Google Analytics event-level data is kept for no more than 14 months. Aggregate reports that no longer identify an individual event may remain available longer.</li>
            <li>Hosting and security logs under my direct control are normally kept for no more than 30 days, unless a security incident or legal claim requires longer retention. Providers may retain technical records for the periods stated in their own policies.</li>
            <li>The record of your analytics choice is kept in your browser for one year. You can change it sooner through Cookie settings.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Cookies and browser storage</h2>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="min-w-full border-collapse text-left text-base">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b border-border text-heading">
                  <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold">Name</th>
                  <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold">Provider and purpose</th>
                  <th class="py-3 font-semibold">Duration</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="align-top">
                <tr class="border-b border-border">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4"><code>matejlukasik_cookie_consent</code></td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">This site, localStorage. Records whether you accepted or rejected optional analytics.</td>
                  <td class="py-3">One year</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-border">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4"><code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_*</code></td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Google Analytics. Distinguishes browsers and measures site usage. Set only after consent.</td>
                  <td class="py-3">Up to two years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4"><code>__cf_bm</code></td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Cal.com / Cloudflare. Bot-management and security cookie loaded with the booking calendar when the Contact page opens.</td>
                  <td class="py-3">About 30 minutes after inactivity</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p>
            You can remove cookies in your browser. Rejecting or withdrawing analytics consent removes analytics cookies that this site can access and stops further Google Analytics loading. The booking security cookie is necessary to display and protect the calendar on the Contact page and is not used by this site for advertising.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            You can ask for access, rectification, erasure, restriction, and portability where the GDPR allows it. You may object to processing based on legitimate interests. You can withdraw analytics consent at any time through Cookie settings without affecting processing carried out before withdrawal. You also have the right to complain to the <a href="https://dataprotection.gov.sk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary font-medium hover:text-primary-hover">Úrad na ochranu osobných údajov Slovenskej republiky</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">No automated decision-making</h2>
          <p>
            I do not use contact, booking, or analytics data for automated decision-making or profiling that produces legal or similarly significant effects.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
